          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "*The monoenergetic neutrons were obtained by bombarding",
                " tritium absorbed in a thin layer of titanium deposited",
                " on a Cu backing with deuterons accelerated up to 1 MeV",
                "*The energy of neutrons was selected by the choice of",
                " the emission angle.",
                "*The neutron energy spread was evaluated from the",
                " effective energy distributions of neutrons incident",
                " on the samples,wich were calculated by the Monte Carlo",
                " method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DG"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 80 cm3 volume",
                "The relative efficiency was determined with use of",
                "standard radioactive sources Yb-169 and Ra-226."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The fluctuations of the neutron flux during",
                "irradiation were monitored by counting protons",
                "recoiling from a thin polyethylene foil,with the use",
                "of Cs(Tl) scintillation crystal in a multiscaler mode."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "* The final results were corrected for summing of",
                "  pulses in the Ge(Li) crystal due to cascading",
                "  gamma-rays in the samples.",
                "* Corrections due contributions of multiparticle",
                "  emission,as well as for deuteron emission in measured",
                "  activities were taken into account."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Given error was due to a statistical error and",
                "several systematic errors among which the most",
                "important are :"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Uncertanty of the reference cross section   3%"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-2",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Error in the integration of the pulse height",
                " spectrum (up to)                                  11%"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-3",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Relative efficiency for detections",
                "                                 of gamma-rays      3%"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-4",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma-ray attenuation uncertainty           2%",
                "Another 10 % error was added due to the correction for",
                "multiparticle emission at neutron energies > 15.5 MeV"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "When reactions on different target isotopes lead to the",
                "same product nucleus a set of differential equations,",
                "describing the production and the decay of the nuclei",
                "of interest have been solved in order to obtain",
                "relations between the investigated and the interfering",
                "reaction cross section;in relation with this were",
                "measured cross section for reactions",
                " Zr-94(n,a)Sr-91 and Zr-90(n,a)Sr-87-m"
              ]
            }
          ],
